Brazil's political crisis appearsto be deepening as powerful state governors are calling for theremoval of Finance Minister Dilson Funaro, chief architect ofeconomic policy.    Commentators said their call, front-page headlines intoday's press, laid bare President Jose Sarney's politicalweakness and highlighted Brazil's economic planning turmoil.    The demand for Funaro's resignation came last night fromfour governors with much combined political clout, those of SaoPaulo, Rio de Janeiro, Minas Gerais and Mato Grosso do Sul. Ata news conference in Sao Paulo, they delivered a blunt message-- the economy was in crisis and they wanted a new ministerialteam to shape policy. Otherwise there was a risk of socialchaos. Reuter&#3;